If applied,

18
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,000
to the problem of atoms in which you do not

19
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:04,000
worry about the motion or the nature of the nucleus,

20
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,000
the structure of the nucleus,

21
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,500
you simply think of the nucleus as

22
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:11,000
a fixed point creating an electric field,

23
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,000
then quantum electrodynamics is also the theory of atoms.

24
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
In the same sense, quantum chromodynamics

25
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
is the theory of quarks and gluons

26
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,000
and the theory, and the things that go with them.

27
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
The things that quarks and gluons make.

28
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
The things that quarks and gluons make are called hadrons.

29
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:35,000
H-A-D-R-O-N-S

30
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:39,000
Hadrons or hadrons.

31
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,500
And they consist of things like

32
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:46,000
protons and neutrons, which are called baryons,

33
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,000
which have a net quark

34
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
number or a net baryon number.

35
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
That means an imbalance of quarks and anti-quarks.

36
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,000
Three quarks for the proton,

37
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:55,000
three quarks for the neutron,

38
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:58,000
three quarks for the neutron.

39
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:03,000
And mesons, which are quark-anti-quark pairs.

40
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:07,000
And all of them are full of gluons.

41
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Gluons are the electrically neutral stuff,

42
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,000
which is the glue and the binding

43
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,000
stuff that holds the quarks and gluons together,

44
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,500
much the same way that

45
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:23,000
the electromagnetic field or Coulomb field

46
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:28,000
is the binding agent that holds atoms together.

47
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:33,000
Atoms, other electrostatically bound objects.

48
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Alright, but before we go into it,

49
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,000
I want to remind you a

50
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:41,000
little bit about the mathematics of spin.

51
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Because, first of all, that particular

52
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,000
mathematics will come up in another guise,

53
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:51,000
but also a simply related mathematics to it

54
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
will also come up,

55
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
in the guise of a quantity called color,

56
00:02:56,000 --> 00:03:01,000
or a concept called color.

57
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:04,000
We're not going to do group theory in this class.

58
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Alright, we'll try to finesse it.

59
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:11,000
But the basic mathematics of what

60
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:15,000
we're talking about is group theory.

61
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
As I said, I'm not going to use group theory,

62
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,000
or at least not call it

63
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,000
group theory as we use it.

64
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:25,500
For spin, the theory of spin

65
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:29,000
is the theory of a group.

66
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,500
A group, if you don't know

67
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:34,000
what a group is, just ignore it.

68
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Alright, but the group is

69
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,000
the group of rotations of space.

70
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,500
The theory of spin is also

71
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:45,000
the theory of the symmetry of physics

72
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:49,000
with respect to rotations of space.

73
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:50,000
But, uh,

74
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,500
we finesse that by not

75
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,000
talking about the theory of rotations,

76
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:59,000
but by talking about the theory of angular momentum.

77
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
I'll just remind you very quickly

78
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:05,000
that we derived everything about angular momentum

79
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,000
from some basic commutation relations,

80
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:14,000
which were of the form Lx with Ly

81
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,000
equals I times Lz.

82
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,000
I think there's an h-bar in there, but, uh, yeah,

83
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:23,000
there is an h-bar in there.

84
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
Well, those are the components of angular momentum.

85
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,000
We worked that out last quarter,

86
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:35,000
and we found some rather surprising and interesting things.

87
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Oh, of course, there are three other relations like this,

88
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,000
which are gotten by permuting x to y,

89
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,000
y to z, and z back to x.

90
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,000
I won't write them down.

91
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:48,000
But when we, um,

92
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
worked out the consequences of this,

93
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
first of all,

94
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,000
we broke the symmetry.

95
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Now, when I say we broke the symmetry,

96
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,000
I'm not talking about something, uh,

97
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,000
some symmetry breaking in nature.

98
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Just we broke the symmetry in our mathematical description.

99
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:08,000
The symmetry being the symmetry of rotation,

100
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
or the symmetry, uh, which interchanges

101
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,000
x, y, and z, and so forth.

102
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,000
We broke it in our heads,

103
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,000
maybe not in the real physics,

104
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:20,000
but just by focusing on the z component of spin,

105
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,000
or on the z component of angular momentum.

106
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
We basically focused on it.

107
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:28,000
We cannot measure all three components simultaneously.

108
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,000
They don't commute with each other.

109
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Here they are. They don't commute with each other.

110
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:34,000
At most, one of them commutes with itself.

111
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Well, of course it commutes with itself.

112
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,000
And no two of them commute.

113
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,000
So at most, you can

114
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,000
talk about one of them, uh,

115
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,000
or measuring one at a time,

116
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,000
and we arbitrarily chose Lz.

117
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:49,000
When we did that and used these commutation relations,

118
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:53,000
what we found was, first of all,

119
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,000
that L is quantized.

120
00:05:55,000 --> 00:06:00,000
And the difference between neighboring values of L

121
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:05,000
was always one unit in units of h-bar.

122
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Number one.

123
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:11,000
Number two, we focused on spin.

124
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:15,000
And we described different,

125
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,000
different spin possibilities.

126
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,000
The first set of spin possibilities

127
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,000
were the half-spin objects,

128
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:24,000
or the things which we call fermions.

129
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,000
Those were the objects whose spin

130
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,000
was centered about zero

131
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,000
in such a way that the first level,

132
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:36,000
the first z component of spin was a half,

133
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,000
and the first one in the opposite direction

134
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,000
was minus a half.

135
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Three halves, minus three halves, and so forth.

136
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Those were fermions, but right now,

137
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:50,000
the main point was that the mathematics of spin,

138
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,000
or angular momentum,

139
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,000
gave rise to some multiplets.

140
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
There was first the spin half multiplet.

141
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:03,000
That was the multiplet with a spin minus a half

142
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,000
and a spin plus a half,

143
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:10,000
like the spin of the electron.

144
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:14,000
That was associated with half-spin particles and fermions.

145
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,000
Bosons, which for our purposes now,

146
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:19,000
just think integer spin,

147
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,000
the first one was just spin zero.

148
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
There are particles with spin zero,

149
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,000
they have no spin, that's all,

150
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:28,000
they just have no spin at all.

151
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Then, there are particles with spin one.

152
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,000
The photon is a spin one particle.

153
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,000
There are other spin one particles.

154
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:37,000
There are nuclei and atoms of spin one.

155
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:40,000
And they have three states.

156
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Plus one, minus one,

157
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,000
in units of h bar,

158
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,000
and zero.

159
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:49,000
And then, the next interesting family

160
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,000
has spin three halves.

161
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:55,000
Spin three halves again goes on the half-spin column here,

162
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:58,000
and that has one half, minus one half,

163
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:02,000
three halves, minus three halves.

164
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:05,000
There are particles with spin three halves.

165
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:10,000
There are certainly nuclei with spin three halves,

166
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
and atoms with spin three halves.

167
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,000
So these things also exist.

168
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,000
Likewise, what comes after spin one?

169
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:19,000
Spin two.

170
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,000
Spin two, spin zero, spin one,

171
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:26,000
spin minus one, or the z component of spin one,

172
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,000
minus one, two, and minus two.

173
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:32,000
These labels here are the z components of the spin.

174
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:39,000
Now, when you speak about an object of spin L,

175
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,000
L is the notation that

176
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,000
denotes the height of the spin.

177
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:47,000
The highest value of z component of spin.

178
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:50,000
So this would be, or M, you can use M.

179
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
Ordinarily, it's used M.

180
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:55,000
M or L, it doesn't matter.

181
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Let's use L.

182
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
Let's use L.

183
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,000
L is a little bit different than M.

184
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,000
When you speak of spin L,

185
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:08,000
you're speaking about an object whose maximum spin

186
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:11,000
along the z axis is L.

187
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:13,000
So this would be spin a half,

188
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,000
L equals a half.

189
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:18,000
This one would be L equals one,

190
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,000
and so forth.

191
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,000
How many states are there?

192
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,000
How many independent states are there

193
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:29,000
for a spin, a particle with spin L?

194
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,000
2L plus one.

195
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,000
2L plus one.

196
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,000
For example, for spin a half,

197
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:40,000
twice L is one, plus one is two.

198
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Two states.

199
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,000
If L is one,

200
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,000
twice one is two.

201
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,000
Add one more, that's three.

202
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,000
Three states.

203
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:53,000
And so 2L plus one is the number of states

204
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:03,000
is the number of independent

205
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:08,000
spin states

206
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
for a given value of,

207
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:12,000
for a given value

208
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:15,000
of L.

209
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:18,000
So that's something I want you to remember.

210
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,000
Now, another thing.

211
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,000
If you have more than one particle,

212
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:29,000
such as an electron,

213
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,000
then you have two spins.

214
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:34,000
Spins can be combined.

215
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Let's consider what you can make

216
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,000
in the way of spin

217
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:42,000
by combining together the spins of two electrons.

218
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:45,000
Let's forget the fact that electrons

219
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,000
can orbit around each other.

220
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,000
Let's ignore what's usually called

221
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,000
orbital angular momentum

222
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:54,000
and just concentrate on the spin angular momentum.

223
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,000
What kind of angular momentum can you make

224
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:02,000
for two half-spin particles?

225
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Well, the maximum value

226
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:09,000
of the z component of spin

227
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,000
is what?

228
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,000
One.

229
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,000
One.

230
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,000
In units of h-bar.

231
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,000
Let's forget h-bar now.

232
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,000
When I say unit,

233
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,000
in maximum spin,

234
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,000
I mean in units of h-bar.

235
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,000
The maximum spin you can have

236
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
along the z-axis is one.

237
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,000
That's when both spins are pointing

238
00:11:25,000 --> 00:11:26,000
along the same,

239
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,000
when both spins are pointing upward

240
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,000
along the z-axis.

241
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:32,000
That axis is the z-axis.

242
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:36,000
So you can have angular momentum one.

243
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:39,000
You can have angular momentum minus one.

244
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:44,000
And you can also have angular momentum

245
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:47,000
or z component of angular momentum zero.

246
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:50,000
But in fact, you can have two states

247
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:53,000
where the z component of angular momentum is zero.

248
00:11:53,000 --> 00:12:00,000
This one and that one.

249
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:01,000
This one and that one.

250
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,000
So there are two states,

251
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:04,000
two independent states,

252
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:08,000
whose z component of angular momentum is zero.

253
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:14,000
How many states are there for a spin one object?

254
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:16,000
Three.

255
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:19,000
Two L plus one.

256
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:22,000
Okay.

257
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:26,000
So there must be a spin one combination

258
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:30,000
because we can make total spin up equal to one.

259
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,000
That's the maximum.

260
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,000
So there must be somewhere there,

261
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:38,000
some combination must correspond to spin one.

262
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,000
What does a spin one have?

263
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,000
It has spin one along the axis,

264
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:46,000
spin minus one along the axis,

265
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,000
and spin zero.

266
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,000
But there are two states with spin zero,

267
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:52,000
with z component of spin equal to zero.

268
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:59,000
They can't both be part of the spin one multiplet.

269
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:05,000
What could the extra one be?

270
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,000
It's got to be,

271
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:08,000
either spin zero,

272
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,000
spin one,

273
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:10,000
spin two,

274
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,000
spin three,

275
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,000
spin four,

276
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,000
spin a half,

277
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,000
spin minus,

278
